    readTime: 10,
    tldr: 'EU personal trainers and small fitness studios often struggle financially despite strong demand for their services, because they undervalue their time, rely too heavily on hourly session revenue without building recurring income streams, and fail to manage seasonal demand effectively. Trainers achieving sustainable incomes above €50,000 consistently combine session work with digital products, group programmes, or studio membership models that generate revenue beyond their personal hours.',
